7 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to venous thromboembolisms screening
and treatment; creating the Blake Burgess Act;
9 requiring certain hospitals to develop and implement
policies and procedures regarding venous
10 thromboembolisms; mandating training for the
rendering of appropriate medical attention for
11 persons at risk of forming venous thromboembolisms;
requiring the State Department of Health to contract
12 with a private entity to establish a statewide venous
thromboembolism registry; providing requirements;
13 requiring hospitals to report certain information
regularly to the statewide venous thromboembolism
14 registry; requiring the private entity to provide
regular reports to the Department on such data;
15 requiring the Department to provide to the Governor
and the Legislature a specified report; providing
16 requirements for report; providing applicability;
amending 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-890.2, which relates
17 to definitions in the Continuum of Care and Assisted
Living Act; adding definitions; amending 63 O.S.
18 2021, Section 1-890.3, as amended by Section 1,
Chapter 357, O.S.L. 2025 (63 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
19 1-890.3), which relates to promulgation of necessary
rules, nursing care component, and adult daycare
20 component; requiring assisted living facilities to
